# IELTS Learning Journey

A fully client-side, offline-first personal IELTS study system. Track vocabulary, reading, listening, writing, speaking, grammar, and mock tests — all in your browser with no backend required. Includes a Chrome extension for collecting learning material from any webpage.

## Features

- **Vocabulary Management** — Add, tag, filter, and review words with SM-2 spaced repetition
- **Skill Tracking** — Log reading, listening, writing, and speaking practice sessions
- **Daily Study Plan** — Plan and track daily study tasks across all IELTS skills
- **Mistake Notebook** — Record and review mistakes with correction tracking
- **Mock Test Tracker** — Log mock test scores and track band progress over time
- **Progress Analytics** — Charts and stats for study days, hours, skill balance, and band trends
- **Learning Journey Engine** — Weakness detection, review scheduling, next-best-action recommendations
- **AI Tutor Chat** — Messenger-style AI assistant with proactive local messages
- **Exercise Generator** — AI-powered and rule-based exercise generation
- **Content Library** — Built-in IELTS content with versioned updates
- **Browser Extension** — Collect vocabulary, sentences, and articles from any webpage
- **Import/Export** — Full JSON backup and restore with merge/replace modes
- **PWA Support** — Install as standalone app, works offline
- **Dark Mode** — Light/dark/system theme with design tokens

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Framework | React 19 |
| Language | TypeScript 5.8+ (strict mode) |
| Build | Vite 6 |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS 4 + CSS custom properties (design tokens) |
| Routing | React Router v7 |
| Database | IndexedDB (via `idb`) — Repository pattern |
| Settings | localStorage |
| Charts | Recharts |
| PWA | vite-plugin-pwa |
| Testing | Vitest + Testing Library |
| Validation | Zod 4 |
| AI (optional) | OpenAI-compatible REST API via adapter pattern |
| Package Manager | pnpm workspaces |

## Architecture

The project follows **Clean Architecture** with four layers, organized as a pnpm monorepo:

```
apps/
├── web/              # React SPA (PWA)
└── extension/        # Chrome extension (Manifest V3)

packages/
├── ui/               # Shared UI components
├── theme/            # Design tokens & CSS variables
├── types/            # Domain entities & Zod schemas
├── storage/          # IndexedDB repositories & migrations
├── ai/               # AI provider adapters & prompt builders
├── learning-engine/  # Business rules & calculations
├── content/          # Built-in content library & seeding
├── exercises/        # Exercise models & strategies
├── import-export/    # Backup/restore logic
├── config/           # Centralized constants
└── utils/            # Pure utility functions

features/             # Feature modules (Presentation + Application)
├── ai-tutor/         # AI Tutor chat widget
├── dashboard/        # Dashboard overview
├── vocabulary/       # Vocabulary management
├── reading/          # Reading practice
├── listening/        # Listening practice
├── writing/          # Writing practice
├── speaking/         # Speaking practice
├── grammar/          # Grammar notes
├── mistakes/         # Mistake notebook
├── exercises/        # Exercise system
├── content-library/  # Content library
├── analytics/        # Progress analytics
├── settings/         # App settings
├── planner/          # Daily study planner
├── onboarding/       # First-run onboarding
└── import-export/    # Import/export UI
```

See [docs/architecture.md](docs/architecture.md) for detailed architecture documentation.

## Prerequisites

- **Node.js** >= 18
- **pnpm** >= 8

## Installation

```bash
git clone <repo-url>
cd ielts-journey
pnpm install
```

## Usage

